docs.abstract: The Miskatonic Institute of Horror Studies in Brooklyn is examining the new golden age of horror, as films like “Get Out” strike the raw nerves exposed by Black Lives Matter and #MeToo.

docs.lead_paragraph: A figment of H. P. Lovecraft’s wicked imagination, Miskatonic University is the Harvard of his horror stories. It appears to be a typical New England college, but elements of the occult are never far from the surface.

docs.abstract: In some remote Aboriginal communities, judges and lawyers arrive by plane and handle dozens of cases in a single day. Critics say language barriers and the rapid pace infringe on human rights.
docs.snippet: In some remote Aboriginal communities, judges and lawyers arrive by plane and handle dozens of cases in a single day. Critics say language barriers and the rapid pace infringe on human rights.
docs.lead_paragraph: WADEYE, Australia — After an hourlong flight over the ocher sands of northern Australia, the judge stepped off the plane and made her way to the makeshift courthouse, a single white-walled room next to a new $20 million police station ensconced in barbed wire.

headline.main: ‘Like a Cattle Yard’: How Justice Is Delivered in Australia’s Bush Courts
headline.print_headline: ‘Like a Cattle Yard’: Justice in the Remote Courts of Australia

docs.abstract: The filmmaker David Siev chronicles his family’s struggle to keep their Michigan restaurant afloat through the pandemic in this hermetic documentary.
docs.snippet: The filmmaker David Siev chronicles his family’s struggle to keep their Michigan restaurant afloat through the pandemic in this hermetic documentary.
docs.lead_paragraph: A ways into the documentary “Bad Axe,” David Siev’s pandemic family portrait, the director’s mother, Rachel, lashes out at him. “David, you don’t live here,” she says. “You don’t have a clue.”

docs.abstract: The legislation has an eye-catching acronym, CAREN, and would allow lawsuits against people who are motivated by bias when calling the police.
docs.snippet: The legislation has an eye-catching acronym, CAREN, and would allow lawsuits against people who are motivated by bias when calling the police.
docs.lead_paragraph: The San Francisco board of supervisors on Tuesday unanimously approved legislation aimed at cracking down on frivolous calls to 911 against people of color, a move that will make it the latest city to enact an ordinance against racist calls to the police.

headline.main: San Francisco Takes Action on Racial Profiling in 911 Calls
